      • getPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_hideForRadiusGreaterThan

        public long getPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_hideForRadiusGreaterThan()

      • setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_hideForRadiusGreaterThan

        public void setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_hideForRadiusGreaterThan(long pointPOIsLevelOfDetail_hideForRadiusGreaterThan)
        This parameter controls if point POIs should be hidden if current map radius is greater than given value. Can be set to null, meaning the point POIs are always visible. By default it's set to 50 to enable hiding of point POIs.

        Point POI - POIs without a room associated with it that appear as a single icon, such as ATMs, Escalators, Charging Stations, etc.

        Parameters:
        pointPOIsLevelOfDetail_hideForRadiusGreaterThan -

      • getPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromRadius

        public long getPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromRadius()

      • setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromRadius

        public void setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromRadius(long pointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromRadius)
        This parameter controls whether point POIs should be scaled when the map radius changes.

        There are four relevant values: setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromRadius(long) setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromScale(double) setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_toRadius(long) setPointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_toScale(double)

        This means that for map radius >= 40 the scale should be 1, between 40 and 15 the scale should be scaled linearly from 1 to 0.6 and below map radius 15, the scale should be 0.6 The above mentioned values are the defaults for this setting. It can be set to null, meaning the point POIs have always the scale = 1.

        Parameters:
        pointPOIsLevelOfDetail_resize_fromRadius -

      • setStartTimeEarliest

        public void setStartTimeEarliest(java.util.Calendar startTimeEarliest)
        For conference room booking, says what is the earliest time of day to allow booking a room.
        Parameters:
        startTimeEarliest - for example the default, 7:00 AM, is specified as follows: startTimeEarliest = Calendar.getInstance(); startTimeEarliest.set(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY, 7); startTimeEarliest.set(Calendar.MINUTE, 0); startTimeEarliest.set(Calendar.SECOND, 0); startTimeEarliest.set(Calendar.MILLISECOND, 0); Note: TimeZone is implied as Venue's timezone, see getStartTimeEarliestInVenueTimeZone(Venue)

      • setStartTimeLatest

        public void setStartTimeLatest(java.util.Calendar startTimeLatest)
        For conference room booking, says what is the latest time of day to allow booking a room.
        Parameters:
        startTimeLatest - for example the default, 6:45 PM, is specified as follows: startTimeLatest = Calendar.getInstance(); startTimeLatest.set(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY, 18); startTimeLatest.set(Calendar.MINUTE, 45); startTimeLatest.set(Calendar.SECOND, 0); startTimeLatest.set(Calendar.MILLISECOND, 0); Note: TimeZone is implied as Venue's timezone, see getStartTimeLatestInVenueTimeZone(Venue)

      • setStartTimeInterval

        public void setStartTimeInterval(int startTimeInterval)
        For conference room booking, the start times are spaced out by this interval, e.g. if 30 then the user has the option to choose 7:00 am, 7:30 am, 8:00 am, etc.
        Parameters:
        startTimeInterval - in minutes (default is 30)

      • getDefaultMeetingDurations

        public java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Boolean> getDefaultMeetingDurations()

      • setDefaultMeetingDurations

        public void setDefaultMeetingDurations(java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Boolean> defaultMeetingDurations)
                                throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        For conference room booking, this declares the options for meeting durations. The defaultMeetingDurations should be declared as a SortedMap where the key is the meeting duration option, e.g. 30 for 30 minutes and the value is a boolean specifying whether it is the default option selected.
        Parameters:
        defaultMeetingDurations - (default [{30, true}, {45, false}, {60, false}])
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a single default isn't specified in defaultMeetingDurations

      • getDateRange

        public int getDateRange()

      • setDateRange

        public void setDateRange(int dateRange)
        For conference room booking, this says how many days into the future should be shown as options for conference room booking. Use in conjunction with setShowSatSun(boolean). The date range is non-inclusive so for example, a dateRange of 7 on a day of the week Wednesday results in showing Wednesday, Thursday, ... Monday, Tuesday. To be clear, the range ends on a Tuesday in the example, not on a Wednesday.
        Parameters:
        dateRange - (default is 7)

        Parameters:
        showSatSun - (default is false)
